  "StockRole": "Ultralight IndustrialMech",
  "YangsThoughts": "Quikscell came up with a clever idea in 3067, sell one cheap chassis and let customers buy different equipment kits for it. Six kits total covering pretty much every industrial job you can think of. Sold everywhere because it was affordable and flexible. Great Houses bought them, backwater planets bought them, mercenaries picked them up for the price. Quikscell stuff is never fancy but it gets the job done and parts are everywhere.",
